"'This is Mr. Jabez Wilson,' said my assistant, 'and he is willing to fill a vacancy in the League.'

"'And he is admirably suited for it,' the other answered. 'He has every requirement. I cannot recall
when I have seen anything so fine.' He took a step backward, cocked his head on one side, and gazed
at my hair until I felt quite bashful. Then suddenly he plunged forward, wrung my hand, and
congratulated me warmly on my success.